This is a "dtla" location inside an office building on Wilshire. I got there 15 minutes early to find parking and still ended up walking 10 minutes from a meter. There is no dedicated parking. Looked like you can't even park in the building if you wanted to (it's gated, gate was closed.) This location seems like it would mostly be useful for people who are already there, so you don't have to park. <Date>1462044711064< /Date><rating>5<//rating>< Text>
Who would have thought that a "dump" could be so cool?  All of Marin Sanitary's operations are top-notch.  They've very environmentally conscious and involved with the community.  They also do a lot with the stuff that's discarded.  The dump area of the facility is clean and always kept up.  It's very, very easy to access.  You just drive through the entry point and pay the fees (reasonable considering how much work they do with the trash), and you can back right up to a location and throw stuff into a large cement "pit".  It's more like your'e just on a loading dock because the "pit" is huge and there's all sorts of equipment and people  constantly clearing it.< /Text>

<Review>I'll start this by saying everyone in this office was very nice and it was overall a pleasant experience. I'll also say this is my first experience with fillers, so I'm not really an authority on this, I'll just give you the details and let you make your own decisions, and I may update this review in the future if I learn more. I went in for one syringe of lip filler and overall am happy with the results, but I do have that feeling they could be better. This practice uses Restylane only, no Juvederm, and on me they used Restylane Defyne. At my two week check in, I saw there was a bit of asymmetry in my top lip. One side is clearly smaller than the other, and the pink part of the lip is noticeably thinner, especially near the corner. I'm sure it's not VERY noticeable, but I'll let you decide if it would bother you. Also, you can see in the pictures it's bumpy on the larger side. There are quite a few lumps in my lips, but the only one that bothers me really is one on the larger side of my top lip where I can tell the bump is shallow, as if it happened as the needle was being pulled out or something. It is visible all the time, even when I smile. The nurse said she couldn't really see what I was talking about on either concern. She did offer to inject some dissolver into the lump, but I opted to just wait for it to get naturally smaller rather than dissolve some of the filler I paid so much for. Neither thing is really THAT noticeable, but it feels like for 500$ they should not happen, although since this was my first time I really have no idea. Even with those issues, I really do love the results and would probably still recommend, however I will probably be trying somewhere new to compare when this filler wears off.

Update: I was called by the office about this review and while I appreciate the follow up, I want to leave this information here for anyone researching different places to get lip filler. She explained to me they cannot save any filler for adjustments as it is illegal and if they were to make adjustments they would open a new syringe, but I didn‚Äôt want to spend anymore money on this at this time. They do offer half syringes which are 300$< /Review>< Response>

I am a 33 year old mother of two toddlers. Proud to say that i breast fed. I have had benign fatty tumors in both breasts since the age 15. These were huge, lemon sized. Being 5'3 and 130 lbs with a 34B bust, I knew once the lumps were removed my breasts would be gone as well. So I scoured the net for a plastic surgeon who would remove the lumps as well as a breast lift and enhancement in one procedure so I wouldn't have to undergo two surgeries and wait to heal in between. I searched for months , but hadn't seen anyone I felt I could trust so I gave up for awhile. Time went by and the lumps began to deform my breast so I couldn't wait longer. This time I found Dr Kaufman.. if you're reading this then you are lucky to have found him too! What a god send. <rating>5< /rating>< text>
I have always thought that people who have plastic surgery are either really rich or have to look really good for their job or both.  And if you can afford it... then what is wrong with getting a little help to feel your best?  However my surgery journey didn't start out that way at all.  I would say that I have always done my best to take care of myself and while my body was not going to be perfect I was ok with it the majority of the time.  Then I had the very unfortunate experience of encountering a life threatening infection called sepsis which left my mid section disfigured and completely "not me."  In order to save my life I lost several internal organs which resulted in a scar that resembled Frankenstein.  On my small frame the sight of it really took over my body and it was all that I could see anymore.  Also, my skateboarding muscles that I so heavily relied on were loose and uncontrollable resulting in me having to give up several sports (i could not balance).  After careful researching I came across Dr. Clark.  I began communicating with the doc and her staff on-line which for me was key because I am very shy and terribly nervous after surviving sepsis.  Dr. Clark and her staff reached out to me and made me feel so comfortable.  When I go into the office I feel like an old friend.  I am about 10 days out post op from my stomach revision or "tummy tuck."  So far I am so pleased with my results although I am currently going through swell hell right now which is completely normal for this stage of the process.  The surgery itself was such a breeze...I talked with Dr. Clark right there at my bedside and that is the last thing I remember...which was good for me!  Dr. Clark and her staff are turning my horrible sepsis memories into positive healing memories as a conclusion to my sepsis.  I have so much gratitude for the care I have received at this surgery center.  I felt completely safe, have a woman doctor, and am healing in a positive direction.  For me, it's the mixture that dreams are made of...but lucky me... it's my real life.  :)</text>

< Text>
Every experience from phone inquiries to 6 month post op was a great one. I have always wanted breast implants; even more so after having my daughter. Things just went almost concave after breast feeding. I told the doc exactly what I wanted and my results far surpassed what that was. I just wanted confidence to wear women's clothing, to feel like I looked sexy when I looked at myself in the mirror. After 27 years I finally have that thanks to Dr. Kaufman. I can't remember the girl that I talked to on the phone the first time but she is what really one me over to actually go have a consult (when I remember I will update). I opted for a "virtual consult" first because I was still on the fence and having anxiety about going in. Basically they tell you to take pictures of yourself at different angles- I was skeptical at first but I figure it's natural(for now) human anatomy... she called me back the next day relaying the message that Dr. Kaufman was extremely excited and hoped to work with me, she shared her personal experience and really gain my trust in one phone call. Next was the pre-op appointment. In short they give you a bra far to big for your girls and give you implants to "try on" as well as a tank top to get the illusion. I was told at this appointment that I'd be luck if I could get 350cc high profile because of my lack of tissue. While I was getting prepped for the OR the Dr. came in the chat and I remember telling him the "bigger the better!" I am proud to say that no longer am I a member of the itty bitty committee because I have 380cc of high profile self confidence! I love them and I love the way I look in tshirts now because you don't have to see my face to know it's a girl wearing it! Thanks to everyone for making me feel at home every step of the way. For the record I did the "under boob" incision and got my implants under my muscle.< /Text>

<user_name>Raul Castro</user_name>< Pics>
None</Pics>
<Text>I usually don't like to post bad reviews, but this place was just not very good.
My wife had heard that it was supposed to be good, so we went.
The ambience was very average, hole-in-the-wall, which I usually don't mind when the food is good. Too bad the food couldn't make up for it.
We got the chicken tortilla soup, a few soft tacos, a few crunchy tacos, and a quesadilla. Not one thing was close to being good, which is too bad. Could not even finish the food we got, it was just plain bad.
I honestly don't understand how this place is rated so highly. They use microwaves to heat up a lot of their food. I could do that at home and it would be just as good, or bad, actually.<//Text><gmapID>0x80c27ed6e7523c25:0x40b5d505f2f12800< /gmapID>< response>

< Review>
A cool University sponsored store to buy premium Chico State products.  The primary products available are authentic CSU clothing. You can also find everything a student needs for school,  such as CSU logo printed planners, high quality backpacks and professional grade office supplies (art/drafting) and related "office supplies." Expect quality and exclusive Chico State products and concordantly higher prices.  You won't find the words "value" "discount" or "sale"  in the Chico State Bookstore.<//Review>

<Rate>1<//Rate>< text>
Books are insanely expensive to both buy and rent, I was a freshman last year and you are required to leave the dorms on fridays before break, well of course I had multiple finals on friday and didn't have time to return the textbooks after the tests and before my shuttle for the airport took off. I had to make the decision to reach my flight and try returning the books a different time. I called the school to let them know what the issue was and instead of understanding the situation they put me in they had me pay a $300 fine for a $100 rental. My advice would be skip the store here and save yourself time and money on a alternative textbook site. Chegg and amazon are great places to start your search. (I understand that it was my fault not turning in the books before I left, I just thought the school would have had a bit of sympathy for a first semester freshman trying to study and get good grades, rather than sucking even more money out of me.)</text>

< review>
Ordered online. Was not informed that orders take several days to become available. I had done this to make pickup more streamlined and not have to wait in excessively long lines at the beginning of the semester. Instead, orders cannot be cancelled apparently, and after 3 times of arriving to pick up my products on different days, I've officially gotten quite irritated. The only options were wait or purchase in the store, then come back to the store to pick up the online order, then sell it back to the bookstore for presumably less than I had just purchased it for.

Very bad logistics systems in place for order cancellations and returns. In other commercial businesses the request to cancel an order before it's been processed or shipped is absolutely possible. There is no reason this canot be done at the Student Store, that I am aware of, other than lazy people putting the systems together or the profits being higher for not accepting cancellations.

Very disappointed. Will never purchase from the Wildcat Store again unless absolutely necessary or these systems are changed to reflect modern logistical and customer service practices.< /review>

<userid>102656148666481935621</userid><Gmap_id>0x8094e21c8f3ab7b1:0x6b55940fe1daffe9</Gmap_id><user_name>MIcho Rizo</user_name>< Rate>

<Pics>None< /Pics>< Review>
Apparently Ridge Creek Management in all of their infinite wisdom decided to flag my last review so that it would be removed from google reviews. Well good thing I found it's gone so I can copy and paste it again for everyone's visibility and will continue to do so until everyone knows high intellect occurring here - thank you again free speech!!

This is not a review of the course - this is a review of the moronic choices that management decides to make - picture this - you get off of work and try to get in18 late in the afternoon. It's warm and you want to exercise so you decide to walk - as you hit the turn, you want to purchase water - but guess what - the restaurant is closed and you cannot purchase water anywhere - not in the pro shop, can't get water on the course because it's not potable and the faucets are shut off - GENIUS! How does management do it? How did they even receive that position? I wonder if mommy and daddy gave it to their family without a degree of common sense so that they can do something with their lives.

If you come, bring A LOT of water because you won't be able to purchase anything within a 10-mile radius after 5pm because management doesn't want to pay the additional $12/hr to keep someone in the restaurant - or have the foresight to buy water for the pro shop to keep on hand for people who would like to purchase some because more money is bad right?

I feel sorry for the employees there because if this is the level of intelligence that they are dealing with on a daily basis, I can only imagine what high-level genius ideas/rules management is coming up with that employees have to abide by. If anyone is interested, I can start a GoFund me so that we can give them more money to pay their employees to stay past 5pm or to purchase water for the pro shop because clearly the course is not making enough money based on the green fees that they charge.

Stop flagging my reviews just so you and other don't need to deal with the truth!<//Review>

<userid>113006765457839020525< /userid>< text>
This is one of the oldest shopping strip malls in Atascadero. Due to being set above El Camino all of their driveways are sloped up toward the parking lot making it difficult for larger vehicles and anyone with a trailer to have a hard time getting in and out of the parking lot. Otherwise it is a very nice, clean and well kept outdoor shopping space with some outdoor seating and a very nice variety of shops, offices and restaurants.</text>

<UserId.>110429676277295704745</UserId.><Text>If I could give this team more stars, I would!  They are so professional, so courteous, and the only bridal team who was able to make magic happen for me!

When I first went into the Brea location, I was feeling very disappointed in my bridal experience up to that point.  In early January, my fianc√© and I decided that we would finally have a wedding on May 11, 2019 (after a 7 year engagement).  This meant we had to get things together very quickly.  By the time I got to the Brea David‚Äôs store in February, I had been dress hunting at several other bridal boutiques, including other David‚Äôs locations.  Every representative from every store told me I couldn‚Äôt try on any of the dresses I really loved because they wouldn‚Äôt be able to order anything in time for my wedding - and NOTHING could be done about it.  I was crushed.  That was until I met Joanna, the Brea location manager.  I told her my challenges and how I was feeling and she immediately went into hero mode.  She told me I had come to the right place and I didn‚Äôt need to worry because she would help me through it.  She asked me which dress I wanted and pulled it for me to try on.  She also pulled all the right size undergarments for me THE FIRST TIME, just by looking at me, and helped me get into everything.  I was impressed with her already.  The moment I walked out of the fitting room and saw that dress on, I was in love!  And she knew it.  She excused herself to get on the phone with the warehouse and work her magic to make sure she could order that dress in time.  When Joanna came back to deliver the good news, that she would be able to order it for me, I literally cried!  It was my first yes in a world full of no and I was overjoyed!  I said yes to the dress and rang that little bell happier than ever!  I finally felt excited and confident about walking down the isle.  And although the dress I tried on in the store was too small, she ordered the dress for me in EXACTLY the right size.  It fits like a glove.  She is absolutely AMAZING!  Thank you Joanna!

Equally amazing are Jasmine and Leah, who assisted my soon to be mother in law and entire troop of bridesmaids with trying on every dress in the place.  My bridal party has a full range of shapes and sizes.  These ladies brought us every size and helped my girls every step of the way. And last but certainly not least, I would like to give a big shout out to the best alterations lady in the world - the queen Elena!  She is outstanding to work with and has a wealth of knowledge and experience that she brings to the table.  She guided me in my search to find the perfect material to line the top of my dress and met with me many times to evaluate the material/colors I chose to make sure they were right.  I recently had my fitting and alterations appointment with her and she spent 2.5 hours with me, explaining and guiding me through the entire process.  I can say without a shadow of a doubt, you are in GREAT hands with Elena.  She is absolutely meticulous in making sure every detail is perfect.  She listens to your feedback and really strives to ensure you are happy with the end result.  She also makes the experience enjoyable as she is very kind and personable.  Thank you Elena!

Once again, the Brea team is absolutely fantastic and I cannot recommend them enough!  Thank you Joanna, Leah, Jasmine, and Elena!  You have certainly made me one happy bride!

< review>
I was the MOH for my best friends wedding. The attendant (Rebecca) was a bit snippy at first, telling us that the brides requests were too vague and then too specific and telling us we could not bring drinks back, when I then saw most of the other guests had theirs.
Eventually we found a happy medium and the bride walked away with her perfect dress under budget. I think they just need to be a bit more relaxed to people walking in the door. For my friend it was the first bridal shop she'd walked into and was quickly overloaded with  rapid fire questions. I think they just need to slow down and get to know the brides needs before just throwing them headfirst into a rack of dresses and then being exasperated when she's taking her time. We booked a 2 hour slot and finished well within that time (even though we started 15 minutes late).</review>
